data.content:
In MSTest v4, `[ExpectedException]` was removed. Replace it with `Assert.ThrowsExactly<TException>()` (or `Assert.ThrowsException<TException>()`) inline:

```csharp
// Before (MSTest v3)
[ExpectedException(typeof(ArgumentNullException))]
[TestMethod]
public void Validate_NullInput_ThrowsArgumentNull()
{
    Validate(null);
}

// After (MSTest v4)
[TestMethod]
public void Validate_NullInput_ThrowsArgumentNull()
{
    Assert.ThrowsExactly<ArgumentNullException>(() => Validate(null));
}
```

- **`Assert.ThrowsExactly<T>`** – matches the exact exception type.
- **`Assert.Throws<T>`** – matches `T` or any derived type.
- **Async variant:** `await Assert.ThrowsExactlyAsync<T>(() => ...)`.

